An effect of light from far-away galaxies being [bent](general relativity) by massive objects that are closer to us and becoming very distorted.

![](http://astrobob.areavoices.com/files/2011/04/Gravitational-lensing-Abell-383-Hubble-1024x728.jpg)

Used to observe far away objects as well as the lenses themselves -- eg. exoplanets.

